<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1452,1932,2067]" lastBlockId="6.[136,1451,158,220]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="99" pageId="5" pageNumber="98">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,530,1932,1959]" pageId="5" pageNumber="98">Affinities and differentiation</emphasis>
:—Only one species known from 
<collectingCountry box="[907,995,1932,1958]" name="Mexico" pageId="5" pageNumber="98">Mexico</collectingCountry>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Stephani 1916: 965) Hassel de Menendez (1990: 211)" authorityName="Hassel de Menendez" authorityPageNumber="211" authorityYear="1990" baseAuthorityName="Stephani" baseAuthorityPageNumber="965" baseAuthorityYear="1916" class="Anthocerotopsida" family="Anthocerotaceae" genus="Anthoceros" kingdom="Plantae" order="Anthocerotales" pageId="5" pageNumber="98" phylum="Anthocerotophyta" rank="species" species="orizabensis">
<emphasis box="[1006,1267,1932,1958]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="98">Anthoceros orizabensis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Stephani, F." pageId="5" pageNumber="98" pagination="991 - 1008" refId="ref7648" refString="Stephani, F. (1916) Species Hepaticarum Vol. V. Geneve, 991 - 1008." type="book chapter" year="1916">Stephani 1916: 965</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation author="Hassel de Menendez, G." box="[195,568,1968,1995]" pageId="5" pageNumber="98" pagination="201 - 219" refId="ref6143" refString="Hassel de Menendez, G. (1990) Las especies de Anthoceros y Folioceros (Anthocerotophyta) de America del Norte, Sud y Central; la ornamentacion de sus esporas y taxonomia. Candollea 45 (1): 201 - 219." type="journal article" year="1990">Hässel de Menéndez (1990: 211)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(SEM spore micrographs of this species can be found in 
<bibRefCitation author="Hassel de Menendez, G." pageId="5" pageNumber="98" pagination="201 - 219" refId="ref6143" refString="Hassel de Menendez, G. (1990) Las especies de Anthoceros y Folioceros (Anthocerotophyta) de America del Norte, Sud y Central; la ornamentacion de sus esporas y taxonomia. Candollea 45 (1): 201 - 219." type="journal article" year="1990">
<taxonomicName authority="Ibarra-Morales, 2021" authorityName="Ibarra-Morales" authorityYear="2021" box="[1218,1293,1968,1994]" family="Hassel" pageId="5" pageNumber="102" rank="family" status="n. fam.">Hässel</taxonomicName>
de Menéndez (1990)
</bibRefCitation>
, plate 4, fig. 9 on page 212), resembles the spore ornamentation of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stephani (1916:" authorityYear="1005" box="[961,1101,2004,2031]" class="Anthocerotopsida" family="Anthocerotaceae" genus="Anthoceros" kingdom="Plantae" order="Anthocerotales" pageId="5" pageNumber="98" phylum="Anthocerotophyta" rank="species" species="telaganus">
<emphasis box="[961,1101,2004,2031]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="98">A. telaganus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, sharing the smooth strip along the trilete mark. Nevertheless, the smooth strip in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hassel de Menendez" authorityYear="1990" baseAuthorityName="Stephani" baseAuthorityYear="1916" box="[688,846,2040,2067]" class="Anthocerotopsida" family="Anthocerotaceae" genus="Anthoceros" kingdom="Plantae" order="Anthocerotales" pageId="5" pageNumber="98" phylum="Anthocerotophyta" rank="species" species="orizabensis">
<emphasis box="[688,846,2040,2067]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="98">A. orizabensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is incomplete, not reaching the equatorial girdle of the spores; moreover, the distal face of the spore has spines in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hassel de Menendez" authorityYear="1990" baseAuthorityName="Stephani" baseAuthorityYear="1916" box="[799,959,158,185]" class="Anthocerotopsida" family="Anthocerotaceae" genus="Anthoceros" kingdom="Plantae" order="Anthocerotales" pageId="6" pageNumber="99" phylum="Anthocerotophyta" rank="species" species="orizabensis">
<emphasis box="[799,959,158,185]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="99">A. orizabensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, while 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stephani (1916:" authorityYear="1005" box="[1043,1183,158,185]" class="Anthocerotopsida" family="Anthocerotaceae" genus="Anthoceros" kingdom="Plantae" order="Anthocerotales" pageId="6" pageNumber="99" phylum="Anthocerotophyta" rank="species" species="telaganus">
<emphasis box="[1043,1183,158,185]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="99">A. telaganus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a spinose-lamellate reticulated distal face.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1451,1200,1258]" pageId="6" pageNumber="99">
