<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1452,1304,2087]" pageId="6" pageNumber="99">
Other American species that share the smooth strip along the spore trilete mark of the proximal face are 
<taxonomicName authority="Stephani (1916: 998)" authorityName="Stephani" authorityPageNumber="998" authorityYear="1916" class="Anthocerotopsida" family="Anthocerotaceae" genus="Anthoceros" kingdom="Plantae" order="Anthocerotales" pageId="6" pageNumber="99" phylum="Anthocerotophyta" rank="species" species="cavernosus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="99">Anthoceros cavernosus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Stephani, F." box="[272,516,1340,1366]" pageId="6" pageNumber="99" pagination="991 - 1008" refId="ref7648" refString="Stephani, F. (1916) Species Hepaticarum Vol. V. Geneve, 991 - 1008." type="book chapter" year="1916">Stephani (1916: 998)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Stephani (1923: 427)" authorityName="Stephani" authorityPageNumber="427" authorityYear="1923" box="[530,938,1340,1367]" class="Anthocerotopsida" family="Anthocerotaceae" genus="Anthoceros" kingdom="Plantae" order="Anthocerotales" pageId="6" pageNumber="99" phylum="Anthocerotophyta" rank="species" species="caucasicus">
<emphasis box="[530,687,1341,1367]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="99">A. caucasicus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Stephani, F." box="[696,938,1340,1366]" pageId="6" pageNumber="99" pagination="425 - 430" refId="ref7667" refString="Stephani, F. (1923) Species Hepaticarum Vol. VI. Geneve, 425 - 430." type="book chapter" year="1923">Stephani (1923: 427)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Austin (1875: 28)" authorityName="Austin" authorityPageNumber="28" authorityYear="1875" box="[998,1358,1340,1367]" class="Anthocerotopsida" family="Anthocerotaceae" genus="Anthoceros" kingdom="Plantae" order="Anthocerotales" pageId="6" pageNumber="99" phylum="Anthocerotophyta" rank="species" species="fusiformis">
<emphasis box="[998,1144,1340,1367]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="99">A. fusiformis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Austin, C. F." box="[1153,1358,1340,1367]" pageId="6" pageNumber="99" pagination="25 - 29" refId="ref4490" refString="Austin, C. F. (1875) Notes on the Anthocerotaceae of North America, with descriptions of several new species. Bulletin of the Torrey Botanical Club 6 (4): 25 - 29." type="journal article" year="1875">Austin (1875: 28)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Hassel de Menendez, G." pageId="6" pageNumber="99" pagination="201 - 219" refId="ref6143" refString="Hassel de Menendez, G. (1990) Las especies de Anthoceros y Folioceros (Anthocerotophyta) de America del Norte, Sud y Central; la ornamentacion de sus esporas y taxonomia. Candollea 45 (1): 201 - 219." type="journal article" year="1990">
<taxonomicName authority="Ibarra-Morales, 2021" authorityName="Ibarra-Morales" authorityYear="2021" box="[1375,1451,1340,1366]" family="Hassel" pageId="6" pageNumber="102" rank="family" status="n. fam.">Hässel</taxonomicName>
de Menéndez 1990
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Sergio, C. &amp; Draper, D. &amp; Porley, R. D." box="[371,582,1376,1403]" pageId="6" pageNumber="99" pagination="160 - 168" refId="ref7150" refString="Sergio, C., Draper, D. &amp; Porley, R. D. (2020) Three new records of Anthocerotophyta for Western Africa (Sierra Leone) based on spore ornamentation of a specimen collected by A. Harrington, with an emphasis on Anthoceros sect. Fusiformes Grolle. Journal of Bryology 44 (2): 160 - 168. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 03736687.2019.1709022" type="journal article" year="2020">
Sérgio 
<emphasis box="[453,505,1376,1402]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="99">et al</emphasis>
. 2020
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Austin" authorityYear="1875" box="[603,851,1376,1402]" class="Anthocerotopsida" family="Anthocerotaceae" genus="Anthoceros" kingdom="Plantae" order="Anthocerotales" pageId="6" pageNumber="99" phylum="Anthocerotophyta" rank="species" species="fusiformis">
<emphasis box="[603,851,1376,1402]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="99">Anthoceros fusiformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
frequently presents a strap shaped thallus and lacks a pyrenoid in the chloroplasts (
<bibRefCitation author="Hasegawa, J." box="[502,689,1412,1438]" pageId="6" pageNumber="99" pagination="97 - 112" refId="ref5992" refString="Hasegawa, J. (1993) Taxonomical studies on Asian Anthocerotae V. A short revision of Taiwanese Anthocerotae. Acta Phytotaxonomica et Geobotanica 44 (2): 97 - 112." type="journal article" year="1993">Hasegawa 1993</bibRefCitation>
), both characters differentiate it from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stephani (1916:" authorityYear="1005" box="[1138,1282,1412,1439]" class="Anthocerotopsida" family="Anthocerotaceae" genus="Anthoceros" kingdom="Plantae" order="Anthocerotales" pageId="6" pageNumber="99" phylum="Anthocerotophyta" rank="species" species="telaganus">
<emphasis box="[1138,1282,1412,1439]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="99">A. telaganus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Regarding 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stephani" authorityYear="1916" class="Anthocerotopsida" family="Anthocerotaceae" genus="Anthoceros" kingdom="Plantae" order="Anthocerotales" pageId="6" pageNumber="99" phylum="Anthocerotophyta" rank="species" species="cavernosus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="99">A. cavernosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stephani" authorityYear="1923" box="[323,480,1449,1475]" class="Anthocerotopsida" family="Anthocerotaceae" genus="Anthoceros" kingdom="Plantae" order="Anthocerotales" pageId="6" pageNumber="99" phylum="Anthocerotophyta" rank="species" species="caucasicus">
<emphasis box="[323,480,1449,1475]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="99">A. caucasicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, both species have spores with spinose outgrows reticulated at the base with ridges enclosing both lumina and pits on the distal face, and the proximal face with scattered spinose outgrowths, sometimes confluent at their bases (SEM spore micrographs of these species can be found in 
<bibRefCitation author="Hassel de Menendez, G." box="[1036,1327,1520,1546]" pageId="6" pageNumber="99" pagination="201 - 219" refId="ref6143" refString="Hassel de Menendez, G. (1990) Las especies de Anthoceros y Folioceros (Anthocerotophyta) de America del Norte, Sud y Central; la ornamentacion de sus esporas y taxonomia. Candollea 45 (1): 201 - 219." type="journal article" year="1990">
<taxonomicName authority="Ibarra-Morales, 2021" authorityName="Ibarra-Morales" authorityYear="2021" box="[1036,1111,1520,1546]" family="Hassel" pageId="6" pageNumber="102" rank="family" status="n. fam.">Hässel</taxonomicName>
de Menéndez 1990
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Sergio, C. &amp; Draper, D. &amp; Porley, R. D." pageId="6" pageNumber="99" pagination="160 - 168" refId="ref7150" refString="Sergio, C., Draper, D. &amp; Porley, R. D. (2020) Three new records of Anthocerotophyta for Western Africa (Sierra Leone) based on spore ornamentation of a specimen collected by A. Harrington, with an emphasis on Anthoceros sect. Fusiformes Grolle. Journal of Bryology 44 (2): 160 - 168. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 03736687.2019.1709022" type="journal article" year="2020">
Sérgio 
<emphasis box="[136,185,1556,1582]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="99">et al</emphasis>
. 2020
</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stephani (1916:" authorityYear="1005" box="[309,450,1556,1583]" class="Anthocerotopsida" family="Anthocerotaceae" genus="Anthoceros" kingdom="Plantae" order="Anthocerotales" pageId="6" pageNumber="99" phylum="Anthocerotophyta" rank="species" species="telaganus">
<emphasis box="[309,450,1556,1583]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="99">A. telaganus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the spores present blunter papillate projections and an incomplete reticulum on the distal face, while the proximal face presents spinose-lamellate projections that are tipped by a papilla.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1452,1304,2087]" pageId="6" pageNumber="99">
In the location here reported, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stephani (1916:" authorityYear="1003" box="[524,637,1628,1655]" class="Anthocerotopsida" family="Anthocerotaceae" genus="Anthoceros" kingdom="Plantae" order="Anthocerotales" pageId="6" pageNumber="99" phylum="Anthocerotophyta" rank="species" species="subtilis">
<emphasis box="[524,637,1628,1655]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="99">A. subtilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be differentiated from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stephani (1916:" authorityYear="1005" box="[945,1086,1628,1655]" class="Anthocerotopsida" family="Anthocerotaceae" genus="Anthoceros" kingdom="Plantae" order="Anthocerotales" pageId="6" pageNumber="99" phylum="Anthocerotophyta" rank="species" species="telaganus">
<emphasis box="[945,1086,1628,1655]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="99">A. telaganus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by spore ornamentation, mature spore color and size, light brown to brown in the first species and black in the second, and smaller spores in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stephani (1916:" authorityYear="1003" box="[1333,1444,1664,1691]" class="Anthocerotopsida" family="Anthocerotaceae" genus="Anthoceros" kingdom="Plantae" order="Anthocerotales" pageId="6" pageNumber="99" phylum="Anthocerotophyta" rank="species" species="subtilis">
<emphasis box="[1333,1444,1664,1691]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="99">A. subtilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Plants not bearing sporophytes are difficult to differentiate. Thalli of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stephani (1916:" authorityYear="1003" box="[905,1119,1700,1726]" class="Anthocerotopsida" family="Anthocerotaceae" genus="Anthoceros" kingdom="Plantae" order="Anthocerotales" pageId="6" pageNumber="99" phylum="Anthocerotophyta" rank="species" species="subtilis">
<emphasis box="[905,1119,1700,1726]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="99">Anthoceros subtilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are smaller and paler in color than those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stephani (1916:" authorityYear="1005" box="[288,428,1736,1763]" class="Anthocerotopsida" family="Anthocerotaceae" genus="Anthoceros" kingdom="Plantae" order="Anthocerotales" pageId="6" pageNumber="99" phylum="Anthocerotophyta" rank="species" species="telaganus">
<emphasis box="[288,428,1736,1763]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="99">A. telaganus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stephani (1916:" authorityYear="1005" box="[442,684,1736,1762]" class="Anthocerotopsida" family="Anthocerotaceae" genus="Anthoceros" kingdom="Plantae" order="Anthocerotales" pageId="6" pageNumber="99" phylum="Anthocerotophyta" rank="species" species="telaganus">
<emphasis box="[442,684,1736,1762]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="99">Anthoceros telaganus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also presents an abundantly lamellate thallus morphotype that could be easily identified in this location.
</paragraph>
